Hi all, I'm having this issue long time ago but I didn't care about it too much, now I really do. The problem is when I use Assimp::Importer or aiImportFile. This will leak memory until the program reachs 1.5 GB and crashes because of bad_alloc  (obviously). I've been testing with the simplest thing but still doesn't work I don't know why. I used classes with char data[0xFFFF] and smart pointers to see if the free was success and it does. But when I go with assimp the memory won't be free.

```
while (true)
	{
		std::cin.get();
		printf_s("created\n");
		ceup<CMesh> test[1000] = { nullptr };

		for (int i = 0; i < 1000; ++i)
		{
			test[i] = std::make_unique<CMesh>();
			test[i]->LoadModel(g_EntityManager->GetEntityPath("cube"), g_EntityManager->GetEntityName("cube"), g_EntityManager->GetEntityFormat("cube"), "def");
		}

		std::cin.get();

		for (int i = 0; i < 1000; ++i)
		{
			test[i].reset();
		}

		printf_s("free\n");
	}
```

I'm using this code to test if the memory is free'd or not looking at Task Manager but the memory is never free'd. This is LoadModel:

```
aiScene* m_pScene = nullptr;
Assimp::Importer Importer;

bool CMesh::LoadModel(const char* szPath, const char* szFilename, const char* szFormat, std::string strTexture, std::string strNormalTexture)
{
	std::string strRealName = DEF, strRealBumpName = DEF;
